@startuml user_account_state
!theme plain
title User Account State Chart Diagram

[*] --> Created

Created --> Active : activate()\n[Account activated by admin]

Active --> Suspended : suspend()\n[Temporary suspension]
Active --> Banned : ban()\n[Account banned by admin]
Active --> PasswordReset : requestPasswordReset()\n[User requests password reset]

Suspended --> Active : reactivate()\n[Admin reactivates account]
Suspended --> Banned : ban()\n[Escalate to permanent ban]

Banned --> Active : unban()\n[Admin unbans account]

PasswordReset --> Active : resetComplete()\n[Password successfully reset]
PasswordReset --> Active : resetExpired()\n[Reset token expired]

Active --> Deleted : deleteAccount()\n[Admin deletes account]
Banned --> Deleted : deleteAccount()\n[Admin deletes banned account]
Suspended --> Deleted : deleteAccount()\n[Admin deletes suspended account]

Deleted --> [*] : purge()\n[Account data purged]

' Self-transitions
Active --> Active : login()\n[Successful login]
Active --> Active : updateProfile()\n[User updates profile]
Active --> Active : changePassword()\n[User changes password]

' Failed login attempts
Active --> Active : failedLogin()\n[Failed login attempt]

' Notes
note right of Created
  Account created
  awaiting activation
end note

note right of Active
  Normal account state
  Full system access
end note

note right of Suspended
  Temporary restriction
  Login disabled
end note

note right of Banned
  Permanent restriction
  All access denied
end note

note right of PasswordReset
  Password reset process
  in progress
end note

note right of Deleted
  Account marked for deletion
  Data cleanup pending
end note

@enduml